# Frontend Page Conventions

## Page folder structure

Every page under `gueta-frontend/src/pages/<PageName>/` must follow:

```
<PageName>/
  <PageName>.tsx      # UI only — no business logic
  use<PageName>.ts    # hook — state, effects, handlers, data fetching
  consts.ts           # constants, labels, formatters, initial values
  utils.ts            # pure helper functions
  <PageName>.module.css
```

Examples: `useLogin.ts`, `useMain.ts`, `useHistory.ts`.

Sub-components in a page folder (e.g. `FinanceModal/`) follow the same pattern with their own `useX`, `consts.ts`, `utils.ts`.

## Mantine-only UI

- Never use raw HTML elements (`div`, `span`, `button`, `p`, `h1`, etc.).
- Use Mantine components: `Box`, `Stack`, `Group`, `Text`, `Title`, `Button`, `Paper`, `Table`, etc.
- Forms: `<Box component="form">` is allowed (Mantine Box, not raw HTML).
- Icons: `@tabler/icons-react` with Mantine `ActionIcon` / `Button` sections.

## Separation of concerns

- **Component (.tsx)**: JSX layout and Mantine props only.
- **Hook (useX.ts)**: `useState`, `useEffect`, `useForm`, navigation, API calls, event handlers.
- **consts.ts**: static values, option lists, error messages, `Intl` formatters.
- **utils.ts**: pure functions with no React hooks.

## Component splitting

Split a `.tsx` file when **both** are true:
1. It exceeds **~100 lines**
2. It has **distinct visual sections** (accordion panel, chart group, data table, modal form block, header bar)

When splitting:
- Extract sub-components to `<Page>/components/<Name>/`
- Page `.tsx` becomes a thin shell: calls `useX`, composes children, passes props/callbacks
- Sub-components are **presentational**: props in, JSX out — no `useEffect`, API calls, or navigation
- Hooks / consts / utils stay at the page root
- Do not split hooks/utils unless they exceed **~150 lines** and contain unrelated concerns

## CSS modules — no inline styling

All visual styling belongs in `.module.css` files — not in `.tsx`.

- **Never** use the `style` prop unless there is no CSS alternative (e.g. truly dynamic runtime values).
- **Never** pass sizing/style props to icons (`size`, `stroke`, `color`) — set `width` / `height` / `color` in CSS via `className` on the icon or a parent selector (e.g. `.navButton svg { width: 1rem; height: 1rem; }`).
- **Never** use Mantine style shorthand props (`p`, `px`, `m`, `w`, `h`, `bg`, `c`, etc.) when the value is static — use a CSS module class instead.
- Prefer Mantine CSS variables in modules (`--button-bg`, `--ai-color`, etc.) for component theming.
- App-wide icon size utilities live in `src/styles/icons.module.css`; component-specific icon sizing targets parent classes in that component's module.
- Shared visual rules go in `components/shared/*.module.css` or page-level shared modules (e.g. `authShared.module.css`).
- Page/navbar max-width uses the global `--layout-max-width` CSS variable in `index.css` — do not hardcode pixel values per page.

## Component folder structure

Every extracted component lives in its own folder:

```
<Page>/components/<ComponentName>/
  <ComponentName>.tsx
  <ComponentName>.module.css   # when styles are not shared
  consts.ts                    # optional — component-only constants
  utils.ts                     # optional — component-only pure helpers
  use<ComponentName>.ts        # optional — component-only logic
```

- Import as `./components/<ComponentName>/<ComponentName>`
- Styles shared across sibling components go in `<Page>/components/shared/<Name>.module.css`
- Page-level layout styles stay in `<Page>.module.css`
